## Executive Summary

This document consolidates findings from a correlation analysis of key performance indicators (KPIs) across Nigerian digital advertising campaigns into a single, actionable strategy framework. The analysis examines relationships among budget allocation, impressions, clicks, conversions, click-through rate (CTR), conversion rate, cost per click (CPC), and return on investment (ROI).

The central finding is straightforward but consequential: **the marketing funnel is structurally sound, but financial scale alone does not drive profitability.** Budget and CPC show near-zero correlation with every performance metric, while the sequential funnel — Impressions → Clicks → Conversions — holds statistically strong. This means performance gains are achieved through better execution, not higher spend.

This document is intended to serve as a reference for marketing decision-makers, campaign managers, and strategists seeking evidence-based direction for resource allocation and campaign optimization.

