## Section 1: Understanding the Correlation Matrix

### What Correlation Measures

Correlation coefficients range from −1 to +1 and indicate the strength and direction of a linear relationship between two variables:

| Range | Interpretation |
|-------|----------------|
| 0.7 – 1.0 | Strong positive relationship |
| 0.4 – 0.69 | Moderate positive relationship |
| 0.1 – 0.39 | Weak positive relationship |
| ~0.0 | No meaningful relationship |
| Negative values | Inverse relationship |

### Key Correlation Values at a Glance

| Metric Pair | Correlation (r) | Strength |
|-------------|-----------------|----------|
| Clicks ↔ Conversions | 0.766 | Strong |
| Impressions ↔ Clicks | 0.726 | Strong |
| Clicks ↔ CTR | 0.596 | Moderate |
| Impressions ↔ Conversions | 0.556 | Moderate |
| Conversions ↔ Conversion Rate | 0.507 | Moderate |
| CTR ↔ Conversions | 0.457 | Weak–Moderate |
| Budget ↔ Any metric | 0.000–0.003 | None |
| CPC ↔ ROI | −0.003 | None |
| Conversion Rate ↔ ROI | 0.000 | None |
| CTR ↔ Conversion Rate | 0.005 | None |

These numbers form the empirical foundation for all strategic recommendations in this document.

