## Section 5: Decision-Maker Reference — Priority Actions

The following table consolidates the key findings into actionable decisions, organized by strategic priority.

| Finding | Implication | Recommended Action |
|---------|-------------|-------------------|
| Clicks → Conversions: r = 0.766 | Clicks are the primary conversion driver | Prioritize click quality over impression volume |
| Impressions → Clicks: r = 0.726 | Exposure reliably generates engagement | Optimize creative and targeting to improve click yield |
| Budget ↔ Everything: ~0.000 | Spend level doesn't predict outcomes | Reallocate budget based on channel ROI, not spend size |
| CTR ↔ Conversion Rate: 0.005 | Engagement doesn't guarantee conversions | Invest in post-click experience and landing page optimization |
| CPC ↔ ROI: −0.003 | Cost per click is not a profitability signal | Evaluate ROI per channel, not CPC alone |
| Conversion Rate ↔ ROI: 0.000 | High conversion rate ≠ high profit | Incorporate revenue-per-conversion into performance modeling |
| Impressions → Conversions: r = 0.556 | Weak direct path due to intermediate variables | Use clicks as the primary optimization target, not raw conversions |

