## Section 6: What to Measure Going Forward

To build on the findings of this analysis, organizations should consider expanding their measurement framework to include:

**Revenue and Profitability Metrics**
- Revenue per conversion by channel
- Contribution margin per campaign
- Customer lifetime value (CLV) segmented by acquisition source

**Channel-Level Analysis**
- Channel-specific correlation matrices
- Budget tier analysis (to test for non-linear threshold effects)
- Attribution modeling beyond last-click

**Engagement Quality Indicators**
- Bounce rate on post-click landing pages
- Time-on-site and scroll depth for traffic from each channel
- A composite "quality score" combining CTR, conversion rate, and CPC

These additions would allow more precise explanations of ROI variation and enable more accurate forecasting of campaign performance.

